Actress Regina Daniels has shared photos of her visit to the Alps with her young son, Munir Nwoko. The Alps, located in Europe, is one of the most popular destinations in the world for a variety of outdoor activities including hiking, trekking, climbing and skiing. This incredibly massive mountain range stretches across eight countries, including France, Monaco, Switzerland, Italy, Liechtenstein, Germany, Austria, and Slovenia. The mother-of-one, who is holidaying in Germany with her little man, had recently disclosed her desire to travel the world and the reason it’s important to make it a reality.   Rest in power, says Denrele Edun at Goldie’s graveside     Wizkid ‘Made- In- Lagos’ equals 27-year-old billboard charts…     Sugar daddies don’t bankroll me, says…   - Advertisement - In her post, the Nollywood child star-turned-billionaire noted a visit to the Alps had been on her bucket list adding, the fun was heightened as she had the pleasure of doing it with her son. She shared a couple of lovely fun photos alongside a video and wrote: “Visiting the Alps has always been on my bucket list. “It was so fascinating and will be memorable with my little one, seeing and feeling the snow as well as other activities on the Mountain but of course, it was extremely cold !!!! This experience will sure live rent-free in my head,” she wrote. SPONSORED